article.headline: South Alabama 65, Western Michigan 45
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Levi Rost scored a game-high 18 points to lead Western Michigan to its 22nd consecutive home victory 65-45 Tuesday night over South Alabama. Rost also had a game-high 11 rebounds for Western (8-3) and hit three 3-pointers. Ben Reed added 14 points for the Broncos. Daniel Northern led South Alabama (3-7) with 10 points. The Jaguars, who lost their third consecutive game, hit just 31.3 percent of their shots. They missed 16-of-19 3-point attempts. Mario Jointer was held to nine points (7.9 under his average) and four rebounds (1.4 under). A 15-0 run by Western in the first half put the Broncos ahead for good, with freshman center Joe Reitz (9 points) finishing off a 3-point play for a 20-5 Western lead with 10 minutes left in the half.
